#[[Image:São_Gregório_Magno.jpg|thumb|right|Icon of [[Pope Gregory I|Saint Gregory]] wearing the omophorion]] In the [[Eastern Orthodox]] liturgical tradition, the '''omophorion''' is the distinguishing [[vestment]] of a [[bishop]] and the symbol of his spiritual and ecclesiastical authority. Originally of wool, it is a band of brocade decorated with [[Christian Cross|crosses]] and is worn about the neck and around the shoulders.
